<TITLE> European shares fall early; Axa, Bayer weigh </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 LONDON, Feb 28 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - European shares fell in early trade on Thursday as insurer Axa and drug and chemical group Bayer fell sharply, and mixed company results worried investors already fretting about the US economy. At 0815 GMT, the FTSEurofirst 300 index of top European shares was down 0.3 percent at 1,353.74 points. Axa and Bayer fell more than 3 percent after updates that disappointed investors, while mining group Xstrata slid 4.5 percent on newspaper reports that Vale's bid for the group had run into trouble. Royal Bank of Scotland, Britain's second-biggest bank which last year led a takeover of ABN AMRO, fell initially but then rose 2 percent after posting in-line earnings and raising its dividend. Brewer InBev rose 4 percent to top European winners after its results, and British American Tobacco tacked on 3.3 perce
